Head
: Mandibles falciform, well-developed with internal margin finely serrate, apex pointed (
Fig. 6A
). Each mandible with 2 thick, long basolateral setae. Maxillary palps each 5-segmented, length slightly exceeding bases of forecoxae; labial palps each 3-segmented, short, reaching middle of 3rd segment of maxillary palps. Labrum trapezoidal with base wider than apex, apical area with approximately 12 to 14 pairs of setae; clypeus with 3 pairs of lateral setae. Eyes large, 1 pair of setae in genal area anterior to eyes, another pair on frontal area, 3 pairs of setae posterior to eyes, and another pair on vertex between antennae. Antennal scapes each broad, with group of 5 setae on base and 2 long lateral setae followed by group of 3 short and fine setae on inner side; pedicel without setae; flagellum extremely long, 2x body length and coiled apically (
Fig. 6B
